rComments: Prof was unwilling to provide a break down of final mark. also, it seemed liked he just made up marks based them on his personal preferences.

He is an excellent prof in terms of teaching, very organized, clear grading. No need for reading, all questions on exam will be from his notes. His sense of hummor is not appropriate at all, too many jokes about "female" issues. He should stop that, so uncomfortable.

Frank is probably the funnest professor at UofO. His jokes and examples will make the information more relatable to your life. He cares about his students despite his attitude at times. His exams are easy and his papers are straight forward. Go to class, read the slides, and you will get an A. Even without doing the useless readings.

Absolutely painful lectures, wastes an absurd amount of time on completely irrelevant examples, used to explain simple subjects. I literally used a timer in one of his classes to see how much of the class he wasted, 42% was what  I ended up with. He usually only manages to cover half of the slides he has prepared due to his astonishingly slow pace.

Lectures always move slowly because of annoying and useless examples, often referencing Frank becoming the Queen, drinking Labatt's Blue, or hanging out with "Steve" or "JT". Reads from slides or dictates long definitions which are in the textbooks anyways. Makes you purchase his own textbook. Terrible lecturer, definitely wouldn't take again.

Professor Ohemeng is actually a hilarious, smart, and intelligence person. He has some very dark and inappropriate humour but he cares about his students. Don't bother asking him questions just memorize everything on his slides. He even tells you not to bother with the readings. Makes the classes fun and engages with practical examples.

The opposite of helpful. He tells you one thing in class, then tells you something entirely different when you go to his office. Doesn't look at you when you're trying to talk to him, and is just plain rude.

I don't understand how they let this guy teach. Exams are based on pure memorization, and you have to regurgitate the answers word for word in order to receive full marks. This class is for you if you're a memorizer and is patient with lame jokes.

SO HORRIBLE TO DEAL WITH. Class was fine, received good grade, expectations clear, but extremely rude in responding to emails and questions. Gets in his own way and causes problems for himself and blames the students. Asked a simple class question, ended up hearing all about his stress level and never got the answer. Needs to work on life skills.

He is an overall good prof. His expectations are very clear and his lectures are very easy going because he uses strong examples and integrates humor. Although he re-uses old course outlines which may be a problem for discussion groups and reading schedules
Solid prof. I've never met a prof with clearer expectations of students than him. Just listen to what he says ..he gives sooo many hints. Take his class, seriously!

Frank is really Frank. He is my favourite professor this semester. His lectures are very straight forward, material is interesting and he's really funny. He gets sidetracked often but he's really good. He tells you what to expect on the midterm and sometimes even gives you the questions. DGD's are mandatory and really easy. I would recommend him.

Is that okay? Full stop.  If you are taking a class with Frank make sure you pay attention. However, midterm was very easy. Multiple choice and short answers. The short answers could be found in the multiple section. More of an IQ test then anything...

Would avoid this prof if possible. The class itself is slow.  It is not hard, the material is not difficult. His grading is unclear and illegitimate. He will go out of his way to avoid talking with you about your grades.  He is unbelievably lazy. He repeats the same thing over, and over again. Very unprofessional professor -an A average student

He is a funny prof. He will answer your questions in class but he is not very helpful after class or through emails and not very approachable after class. You have to attend DG's every week. Unfortunatly we had a DG moderator that was knowlegeable but  incomprehensible and was not able to communicate his ideas clearly.

True or false, this prof is full of jokes. Interesting course content, and you will learn a lot. If you study, you will find that the course is also unbelievably easy. Hawreva, he does not appreciate stupidity, and will call you out if he sees that you aren't paying attention, so be careful. Is that okay?

Dr. Ohemeng is a great prof, very knowledgable in the subject area. He is a little difficult to understand at times due to his accent but repeats himself frequently when he notices students are having trouble following. DGDs were very informative and fun, I attended not only because we were marked on them but because I liked them. Would take again!
his lecture is really interesting, he makes things easy to understand with great examples. I would like to take his class again.

He is very enthusiastic,but talks very fast and you need to write out what he is saying because this will be on the exams.So you really have to go to class.DGD was fun,but I went and talked a significant amount at every one and still only got an 80%.So apparently you need to make some major conclusions to get great marks. exam a lot of memorizing!

I liked his class a lot, he is a pretty funny guy, makes the lectures interesting. He gives notes in class that are NOT on the slides. I had fun in the class and would be happy to have a class with him again.

Horrible prof. Gets his horrible ta's to determine your marks for the dgs. Nobody in our class got perfect in their dgs. ex. I attended 4/5 dgs and participated in everyone and got 8/20. Prof wouldn't even reply to my email. Very incomprehensible. Dg marks are a complete sham. Don't take it unless you have to.
